14 Section 2. Section 20-7-104, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "20-7-104. Transparency and public availability of public school performance data -- reporting -
16 - availability for timely use to improve instruction. (1) The office of public instruction shall establish,
17 maintain, and continually improve a statewide K-12 data system that, at a minimum:
18 (a) includes data entry and intuitive reporting options that school districts can use to make timely
19 decisions that improve instruction and impact student performance while creating a collaborative environment
20 for parents, teachers, and students to work together in improving student performance. Options that the office
21 of public instruction shall incorporate and make available for each school district must include data linkages to
22 provide for automated conversion of data from systems already in use by school districts or by the office of
23 public instruction that allow districts to collect, manage, and present local classroom assessment scores,
24 grades, attendance, and other data to assist in instructional intervention alongside the existing school
25 accountability and statewide student achievement results. The office of public instruction shall ensure that the
26 design of the system is enhanced to prioritize collaborative support of each student's needs by classroom
27 educators, administrators, and parents.
